PASSENGER INFORMATION
SAN JUAN AIRLINES schedules are listed in the Official
Airline Guide and has ticketing and baggage transfer ar-
rangements with all major domestic airlines. For reservations,
call any travel agent or major airline. Joint fares are available
to most United States destinations including Alaska and
Hawaii.
RE-CONFIRMATION — Please re-confirm your reserva-
tion on all San Juan flights 24 hours prior to departure.
BAGGAGE - Your baggage can be checked to your final
destination via connecting airlines. Two standard suitcases
(50 Ibs. total) may be checked free. Excess luggage may be
checked "space available" at $5.00 each. Oversize or over-
weight baggage including trunks, duffel bags, golf clubs and
backpacks may be checked "space available"
at $10 each.
CARRY-ON BAGGAGE — Federal regulations do not
permit carry-on baggage to be stowed at the passenger seat
except for handbags, briefcases, or small packages providing
such items fit beneath the seat.
RESTRICTED ARTICLES - Baggage may not contain
corrosives,
explosives, matches, flammable liquids or com-
pressed gasses. All firearms must be declared.
SAN JUAN AIRLINES is not liable for loss of, damage to,
or delay in the delivery of fragile or perishable articles, critical
medicine or health items,
money, jewelry, silverware,
negotiable papers, securities, or other valuables, business
documents or samples or articles not suitable or suitably
packed which are included in checked baggage whether with
or without knowledge of the carrier.
CHILDREN under 2 not occupying a seat are carried free.
Under 12 when accompanied by an adult may travel at 75% of
the applicable adult fare. All unaccompanied children pay full
fare.
CREDIT CARDS - San Juan Airlines accepts Visa and
MasterCharge.
